As the bell rang, the crowd erupted into cheers as Syuri and Saya Kamitani locked eyes, ready to battle for both the World of Stardom Championship and the Wonder of Stardom Championship. Syuri had been on a winning streak for months, her talent and determination earning her the respect of fans and wrestlers alike. Saya Kamitani, on the other hand, was a newer face on the scene, but she had quickly made a name for herself as a formidable opponent.

The two wrestlers clashed, their movements quick and precise as they battled for dominance. Syuri's agility and strength made her a formidable opponent, but Saya Kamitani's powerful strikes kept her on the defensive. Despite the fierce competition, Syuri was determined to come out on top and win the double title match.

But just as it seemed that Syuri was gaining the upper hand, disaster struck. Saya Kamitani attempted her signature move, the Phoenix Splash, but she botched the execution, landing awkwardly on Syuri's nose and breaking it. Blood spurted everywhere as Syuri fell to the ground in pain, but Saya Kamitani was quick to capitalize on the opportunity, hitting the Phoenix Splash again and pinning Syuri for the win.

As Saya Kamitani stood tall in the ring, covered in her opponent's blood, she declared herself the true champion of World Wonder Ring Stardom, and hailed her faction, Queens Quest, as the greatest in professional wrestling history. The other members of Queens Quest came out to celebrate with her, lifting her up on their shoulders as she basked in the adoration of the crowd.

But just as the celebration was reaching its peak, Waka Tsukiyama appeared, her face set in determination. Despite her record of zero wins and 256 losses, she declared that she would beat Saya Kamitani, no matter what it took. Tam Nakano came out to try and talk her down, telling her that she wasn't ready to face someone as powerful as Saya Kamitani, but Waka was undeterred.
